53leee
Singapore, Singapore
7315
Reviewed November 23, 2017
Nice sauce. A little eatery hidden in the alley
We went there upon seeing good reviews on this banh xeo eatery. When we sat down the lady just brought some plates of paper rolls with vegetables. Skewered meat and dipping sauces. We haven't even placed orders:). The menu is small and hence they probably could figure out what customers want to eat so they just brought the food. I ordered the grilled beef in addition. The staff showed us how to wrap up all the ingredients in the paper rolls. The sauce was awesome but I found it quite difficult to eat as all the ingredients keep fallling out and the sauce drips all over.
Date of visit: November 2017
