sophia_n80
London, United Kingdom
5125
Reviewed October 12, 2017
Recycling food!
I was seriously craving banh xeo and was excited to try this famous place. It's very busy so I was expecting great things as we sat near where all the food was being prepared. Then I saw one of the staff clearing a table and putting the leftover veggies and rice paper to one side and serving it again to a new table! This is a great way to spread bacteria and totally unnecessary given how cheap rice paper and veggies are!
